The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on Thanksgiving Day. The proclamation highlights the historical significance of Thanksgiving, starting with the Pilgrims' journey to America and their celebration of a bountiful harvest with the Wampanoag Tribe. It also mentions President George Washington's declaration of a National Day of Thanksgiving and President Abraham Lincoln's establishment of Thanksgiving as a national holiday. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of gratitude and unity, acknowledging the sacrifices made by service members, law enforcement officials, and first responders. It encourages Americans to gather with their loved ones and offer prayers of thanks to God for the blessings they have received. President Trump officially declares November 28, 2019, as a National Day of Thanksgiving.